deck: Chariots are trans-continuum vessels from Heaven with their own intelligence and used by the angels of the Pax Dei where they telepathically communicated to their occupants.
description:
These vessels were created by Heaven for use by the hosts of the Pax Dei and were intelligent craft that communicated telepathically to their operators. This allowed them to brief their angel pilots on important missions and give details on their tasks. They were described as being trans-continuum chariots that were able to manifest in the mortal realm or even allow travel to distant alien worlds. During Asmodel's conspiracy against the Presence, he attempted to silence the guardian angel Zauriel but the Bull Host faced opposition from the Justice League of America. This saw Asmodel personally intervene by manifesting his Chariot on Earth but he was defeated and his rebellion was ended. Afterwards, the Chariot was summoned to stop the empowered Cronus but he simply called it a toy which he destroyed with his sickle.


When the Helmet of Nabu was missing, Malachy of the Pax Dei tasked Zauriel with recovering it from the planet Okoentis. This saw Zauriel being given an Ezekial EL-777 that briefed him on the mission and the target planet when it went through space to deliver the angel to that world.
name: Chariot

deck: This is a weapon of choice used by Tim Drake (a.k.a) Red Robin, in many battles.
description:
The prehensile Bo-staff first appears in the Big Bad World mini-series, when Robin has a run in with Lady Shiva. After training him, (a crash course in all things deadly) Lady Shiva asks the boy to pick any weapon to continue. While there are no blades on the staff, it mirrors Robin's personality as well as his mentor's and predecessor's as a non-lethal tool of maiming. Robin puts in his own little signature into his first wood stick by slightly slicing one edge to give it the sound of a bird whistle when moving.

He also uses this stick against Jubilee in Marvel vs DC/DC vs Marvel.

While the Bo Stick gives the teenager more reach, he can also retract the stick.

deck: A Techno-Seed was an Apokoliptian New God device used to create servant constructs such as Brimstone.
description: These terrible machines from Apokolips had the ability to create constructs designed to serve their master Darkseid. The were able to create magnetic fields and were embedded as the core of a servitor thus serving as a potential weak spot in their bodies. Darkseid commanded DeSaad to prepare a Techno-Seed as part of Operation: Humiliation. This saw the device being sent into the Hudson Nuclear Facility reactor where it formed the creature known as Brimstone. Once formed, the fiery giant proceeded to destroy everything in his path as he deemed it his mission to rid the world of mankind. Task Force X was dispatched by Amanda Waller to destroy the beast after they learned that a machine within Brimstone was generating magnetic fields to contain its fiery plasma based body. deck: In the world of American Flagg, the Plexus Rangers use futuristic weapons with specialized functions.
description:
The Plexus Rangers use a host of specialized weaponry mostly supplied by The Plex through the Jerry Rigg Custom Firearms franchise located in all plexmalls. While most of their weapons are designed for urban pacification and crowd control, some, like the Magrum .666, can be outfitted for more lethal situations.

Standard issue Buzzknucks and Kruncheons are electrified versions of modern day brass knuckles and truncheons. The Rangers commonly use these in riot situations where hand to hand combat becomes necessary. Used with the Lexan riot shield, they are an effective combination for quickly putting down a rioting taxpayer with non-lethal force.

The Magrum .666 Mark of the Beast can be outfitted with rubber bullets or standard .666 caliber rounds. It is the standard sidearm for all Plexus Rangers.

Thermo Jelly is an explosive in gel form, much like a solid version of napalm.

The Snowball 99 also known as Caligari's Equalizer, launches a frozen globe of Somnambutol ("snowball") which is a recreational barbituate that produces instant sleep in industrial concentrations.

Nachtmacher is a riot dispersal chemical developed by Kruppwest Fourthreich Technologies. It generates a darkfield of instantaneous, but limited duration. The rangers use special goggles to function while operating under cover of Nachtmacher.

description: These pills fit within the hand of a human being and when dropped it spread as a vapor that infected individuals with a maddening paranoia. Those that inhaled it became a mad raving maniac that turned against one another and was able to create entire crowds into an unreasonable mob that were capable of killing innocents. Dr. Bedlam made use of a Paranoid Pill as part of a cunning plan to capture Mr. Miracle at Chandlers Tower. Whilst Scott Free was at the top of the building, Dr. Bedlam disseminated the paranoia vapor through the ventilation system and turned all the human occupants into a hostile force. As such, Mr. Miracle was trapped in the building with his only way out being through an entire army of unpredictable hostile humans.

deck: The Wheel of Plagues is an ancient relic hidden beneath the sands of Sudan in Africa that contained the codified formula to create apocalyptic viruses and the secrets of life.
description:
Legacy

This relic was created by an ancient people that once inhabited the world who were old when the likes of Ra's al Ghul were young. This civilization had somehow stumbled on the mysteries of DNA and recombinant genetics. Once learnt, they relegated this to a secret kept among their scientific priesthood who codified this art onto the Wheel which was used as a record for their experiments. This allowed the users of the relic to make use of it as a table needed to configure the structures of micro-organisms, viruses or even plagues. The fate of this society was unknown except that they seemingly disappeared from the world but not before securing the Wheel in an ancient chamber beneath the sands in Sudan. Thus, the large artifact became long lost to the world and became a famed relic for the knowledge written on its surface. At some point, Ra's al Ghul learnt of its existence and spent a hundred lifetimes in search of the Wheel of Plagues in order to create an apocalyptic virus which he could use to cleanse the world of corruption.
name: Wheel of Plagues

description:
Gurren Lagann is the mecha Simon and Kamina pilot in the series Gurren Lagann. Gurren Lagann runs on Spiral Energy and is one of the most powerful mechas in the early episodes of the series, and THE strongest mecha in the series at the end of it. Gurren Lagann is made from two mechas fused with the Lagann Impact . Both Gurren and Lagann were mechas stolen from Beast- Men. Later on in the series, Gurren Lagann fused with an unnamed mecha for a permanent set of spiral powered wings. Gurren Lagann is tremendously powerful; even in its first form.

  • Gurren Lagann easily breaks the Sound Barrier within seconds of taking off for flight.
  • Gurren Lagann could easily lift 100+ tons.
  • Gurren Lagann was able to beat Viral's extremely powerful mecha right after fusing

Arc-Gurren Lagann : The Dai- Gurren ship The ship only responds to Lord Genome as its owner. To fight the Anti-Spiral fleet, Gurren Lagann fused with the Dai- Gurren ship to create the Arc- Gurren Lagann. Although it's full power was never witnessed; on it's debut, it broke the fabric of space and time with brute force. Arc Gurren Lagann is the size of Tokyo and has literally immeasurable strength. Arc-Gurren Lagann has boundless power and is leagues stronger than Gurren Lagann.

Super Galaxy Gurren Lagann: SGGL is another colossal form of Gurren Lagann created by absorbing an ocean of Spiral power. SGGL is the third most powerful form of Gurren Lagann in the series; it is a little bigger than planet Earth. Because of its size, the people on board use teleportation technology to move around the ship. Its combat abilities are unparalleled by any other battleship-type mecha in the series, sporting an enormous array of time- traveling missiles, beam weapons and shielding capabilities. It also has the capability to transverse to other dimensions and universes and has the manufacturing capabilities to create hundreds of Arc-Gurren Lagann-sized mecha in a small period of time. It is as big as Planet Earth. Super Galaxy Gurren Lagann has the power to use Time/Space missiles which can be fired anywhere and will traverse time and space to find their target. The missiles are easily solar system busters.

Tengen Toppa Gurren Lagann: This is the strongest mecha in the anime television series, but there is a stronger form shown in the movies. It's abilities are immeasurable due to it being powered by its pilot's infinite willpower. TTGL's punches are strong enough to obliterate multiple galaxies. It is 100 times the size of the Milky Way Galaxy. It's abilities are drawn mainly from its pilots; guns, lasers, swords, hooks, and obviously, drills. TTGL is strong enough to bend reality, break the laws of physics, create matter from nothing, and take attacks with the power of the Big Bang. TTGL was the biggest mech ever seen in an anime (until it was surpassed by SSTGL in the movies). It moves at billions of times the speed of light and is constantly generating so much energy, a galaxy is being created in its engines.

Super Tengen Toppa Gurren Lagann : The most powerful form of Gurren Lagann in existence. It is hundreds of times taller than TTGL. STTGL is so gigantic that it made all the galaxies around it look tiny. A God-like entity, it is 52.8 billion light years tall, according to the official guide book from GAINAX (仕事魂), making it about 58% the size of the universe (91 billion light years). Its finishing move, Super Tengen Toppa Giga Drill Break, is at least ten times longer than STTGL itself (and several times wider), large enough to engulf a multiverse and strong enough to destroy a multiverse many times over. STTGL moves at speeds not comprehensible to us, traversing trillions of light years in seconds.
name: Gurren Lagann
